message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "satchange: Multipurpose satellite change detection"
# After connecting Zenodo and cutting a release, add the minted concept DOI here, e.g.:
# doi: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX"
# identifiers:
#   - type: doi
#     value: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX"
#     description: "Concept DOI (all versions)"
abstract: >-
  Pure-Python toolkit for satellite change detection — deforestation, mining,
  urbanisation, floods, burns, surface-water change and multi-epoch urban growth
  — from free Sentinel-1/2 and Landsat data via Google Earth Engine or Microsoft
  Planetary Computer (no account needed). Produces georeferenced GeoTIFFs,
  quick-look PNGs, statistics, and print-ready maps.
